  "prompt": "How can I recover data from my broken iPhone?",
  "response": "Recovering data from a broken iPhone can be challenging but here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. **Check Backup Options**:\n   - **iCloud Backup**: If you have enabled iCloud Backup, you can restore your data to another iPhone. Sign in with your Apple ID and select the latest backup during setup.\n   - **iTunes/Finder Backup**: Connect your iPhone to a computer where you've previously backed up your device using iTunes (on Windows or older macOS) or Finder (on macOS Catalina or later).\n\n2. **Use Recovery Mode**:\n   - If the iPhone isn\u2019t turning on properly, try putting it into Recovery Mode and connecting it to a computer to access the data.\n\n3. **Third-Party Software**:\n   - Use third-party data recovery software. Some options include Dr.Fone, iMobie PhoneRescue, or Tenorshare UltData. These tools can help recover data if the device is functional but not booting properly.\n\n4. **Professional Data Recovery Services**:\n   - For severe physical damage, consider professional data recovery services. Companies like DriveSavers or local Apple certified repair centers can often help recover data from broken devices.\n\n5. **Connecting to Another Device**:\n   - If the screen is broken but the phone is otherwise functional, you might be able to access your phone using another device via Bluetooth or with an adapter. For instance, you can connect a mouse through a USB adapter to control the device.\n\n6. **Use Apple Support**:\n   - Contact Apple Support for possible repair services or additional advice tailored to your specific situation.\n\n### Steps in Detail:\n\n**iCloud Backup Recovery**:\n1. Obtain another iPhone.\n2. During setup, sign in with your Apple ID.\n3. Choose to restore from iCloud Backup when prompted.\n\n**iTunes/Finder Backup**:\n1. Connect the broken iPhone to the computer where you\u2019ve backed up.\n2. Open iTunes (Windows) or Finder (macOS Catalina or later).\n3. For iTunes: Click on the device icon, choose \"Restore Backup\".\n4. For Finder: Select your device in the sidebar, click \"Restore Backup\".\n\n**Recovery Mode**:\n1. For iPhone 8 or later:\n   - Quickly press and release Volume Up.\n   - Quickly press and release Volume Down.\n   - Press and hold the Side button until you see the Recovery Mode screen.\n   \n   For older models:\n   - For iPhone 7 or 7 Plus: Hold Volume Down and the Sleep/Wake button.\n   - For iPhone 6s or earlier: Hold the Home button and the Sleep/Wake button together.\n2. Connect the device to your computer.\n\n**Third-Party Software**:\n1. Install the chosen software on your computer.\n2. Follow the instructions provided to connect your device and start the recovery process.\n\n**Professional Services**:\n1. Search for local or online professional data recovery services.\n2. Send or bring your device to them for evaluation and potential data recovery.\n\nRemember to always regularly back up your iPhone to avoid data loss in the future.",
